annotationA: TBP-related factor (Trf) is ubiquitiously expressed but upregulated in the central nervous system and the gonads of developing Drosophila. In flies the majority of Trf substitutes for Tbp in Pol III transcription in complex with Brf. The rest of Trf initiates transcription of a small subset of PolII-transcribed genes regulating fly fertility and nervous system function
annotationB: TBP-associated factor 12 (Taf12) is part of the multisubunit basal transcription factor TFIID, and it is important for its stability. It forms a histone-like pair with Taf4. Taf12 is also an integral component of the Drosophila SAGA histone acetyltransferase complex
